  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Transport 1,500 blood donors to save 4,500 lives</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">34% of maternal deaths in Kenya are a result of blood shortage. These deaths are preventable! Kenya&apos;s blood banks are beginning to run dry. The country relied for years almost entirely on U.S. aid but the funding was discontinued.  We formed RedSplash to avail safe and free blood to all patients on time. We collected over 3,000 units of blood from 2019. But we lose 1 for every 2 donors recruited because they don&apos;t have the fare to commute. Paying $2-3 moving to the hospital is costly for donors.</narrative>
  </description>
